"Who ya gonna believe, me or your lying eyes?" - Groucho Marx, Duck Soup While the focus of Robinhood traders is on the exciting yo yo action and near gambling over the speculative shiny objects (du jour) and some other traders focus on the market's near term price momentum

(even though the S&P is at the same level of early June) -- some fundamental investors (like myself) are looking more closely to the flattening high frequency economic data and the rising chorus of company executives who over the last few days have been flagging economic and

market uncertainties. Specifically, the managements of Citigroup (C) , Wells Fargo (WFC) , JPMorgan (JPM) and Goldman Sachs (GS) all echoed the same mantra - that they are surprised how optimistic the economic and business forecasts have grown and how enthusiastically the
